<title>USA: Cerplex Group says to cut staff in north.</title>
<headline>Cerplex Group says to cut staff in north.</headline>
<dateline>TUSTIN, Calif. 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cerplex Group Inc said Friday it will eliminate 125 jobs by cutting its North America staff by 16 percent.</p>
<p>The company said the move, which will yield annualized cost reductions in excess of $7 million, is part of a plan for its return to profitability.</p>
<p>The company said it would close its Poughkeepsie, N.Y. operation and relocate it to its Lawrence, Mass. site.</p>
<p>The company also said it plans to consolidate its Redmond, Wash. and Tustin operations.</p>
<p>Service programs at these two sites will transfer to the company's operations in Northern and Southern California, Kentucky, and Massachusetts.</p>
